{"key":"post-16115373","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16115373</id>\n<content>I've long recommended running a PC at 14 psi so it doesn't run dry.&amp;nbsp; If you keep the stove setting too high, not only does it make a horrible racket, but it dries out the substrate in your jars, and will boil out the water in the pressure cooker too.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The important thing is to keep the weight/rocker off the nozzle until steam has escaped for ten minutes or so at the start of the cycle.&amp;nbsp; This replaces all the air in the PC with steam, which is critical.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16116288</next>\n<prev>16114261</prev>\n<first>16113829</first>\n<last>16116288</last>\n<when>1334930754</when>\n<utime>04/20/12 05:05 PM</utime>\n</post>"}